Date: 1998-10-26

Title: Non-tachyonic open descendants of the 0B string theory

Comments: 13 pages, Latex. Minor corrections. Final version to appear on

Phys.Lett.BJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B444 (1998) 309-317

We use the crosscap constraint to construct open descendants of the 0B stringcompactified on $T^6 /Z_3$ and on $T^4/Z_2$ free of tachyons both in the closedand in the open unoriented sectors. In four dimensions the construction resultsin a Chan-Paton gauge group $U(8)\otimes U(12)\otimes U(12)$ with threegenerations of chiral fermions in the representations$(\overline{8},1,\overline{12}) +(8,12,1)+(1,\overline{66},1)+(1,1,66)$.